text.__SUMMARY__: Ondina dilucida is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pyramidellidae, the pyrams and their allies.
text.Description: The length of the shell varies between 1.6 mm and 2.4 mm.
text.Distribution:
This species occurs in the following locations at depths between 125 mm and 500 m:
European waters (ERMS scope)
Portuguese Exclusive Economic Zone
Spanish Exclusive Economic Zone
Atlantic Ocean: Canary Islands
Mediterranean Sea (Algeria)
